    {
        "content": "<p>I suggest to have a look at Nova, which does the same thing, just with a DRM instead of UIO device.</p>\n<p>What I'm doing there is, put all the driver private data (including the <code>Devres&lt;pci::Bar&gt;)</code> into the DRM device and then put the DRM device into the PCI private driver data [1].</p>\n<p>Note that a DRM device is reference counted, so the lifetime of the DRM device is not bound on the PCI private driver data. Also note that <code>data</code> is an <code>Arc</code> because a DRM device is allowed to outlive the driver.</p>\n<p>[1] <a href=\"https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/drm/nova/-/blob/nova-next/drivers/gpu/drm/nova/driver.rs?ref_type=heads\">https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/drm/nova/-/blob/nova-next/drivers/gpu/drm/nova/driver.rs?ref_type=heads</a></p>",
        "id": 488666568,
        "sender_full_name": "Danilo Krummrich",
        "timestamp": 1734019197
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"671004\">Danilo Krummrich</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/UIO.20device.20abstraction/near/488666568\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I suggest to have a look at Nova, which does the same thing, just with a DRM instead of UIO device.</p>\n<p>What I'm doing there is, put all the driver private data (including the <code>Devres&lt;pci::Bar&gt;)</code> into the DRM device and then put the DRM device into the PCI private driver data [1].</p>\n<p>Note that a DRM device is reference counted, so the lifetime of the DRM device is not bound on the PCI private driver data. Also note that <code>data</code> is an <code>Arc</code> because a DRM device is allowed to outlive the driver.</p>\n<p>[1] <a href=\"https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/drm/nova/-/blob/nova-next/drivers/gpu/drm/nova/driver.rs?ref_type=heads\">https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/drm/nova/-/blob/nova-next/drivers/gpu/drm/nova/driver.rs?ref_type=heads</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This would work for me， I will try tonight</p>",
        "id": 488748906,
        "sender_full_name": "JCKeep",
        "timestamp": 1734053792
    }
